{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":637,"text":"Democracy is in trouble, no question about that,"},{"time":4140,"text":"and it comes in part from a deep dilemma"},{"time":7398,"text":"in which it is embedded."},{"time":10070,"text":"It's increasingly irrelevant to the kinds of decisions"},{"time":13817,"text":"we face that have to do with global pandemics,"},{"time":17342,"text":"a cross-border problem;"},{"time":19451,"text":"with HIV, a transnational problem;"},{"time":22874,"text":"with markets and immigration,"},{"time":24949,"text":"something that goes beyond national borders;"},{"time":27503,"text":"with terrorism, with war,"},{"time":29776,"text":"all now cross-border problems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":32423,"text":"In fact, we live in a 21st-century world"},{"time":36178,"text":"of interdependence,"},{"time":38383,"text":"and brutal interdependent problems,"},{"time":41906,"text":"and when we look for solutions in politics and in democracy,"},{"time":47550,"text":"we are faced with political institutions"},{"time":50738,"text":"designed 400 years ago,"},{"time":54191,"text":"autonomous, sovereign nation-states"},{"time":58669,"text":"with jurisdictions and territories"},{"time":61231,"text":"separate from one another,"},{"time":62990,"text":"each claiming to be able to solve the problem"},{"time":65923,"text":"of its own people."},{"time":67996,"text":"Twenty-first-century, transnational world"},{"time":71292,"text":"of problems and challenges,"},{"time":73034,"text":"17th-century world of political institutions."},{"time":77010,"text":"In that dilemma lies the central problem of democracy."},{"time":83390,"text":"And like many others, I've been thinking about"},{"time":85236,"text":"what can one do about this, this asymmetry"},{"time":88704,"text":"between 21st-century challenges"},{"time":90697,"text":"and archaic and increasingly dysfunctional"},{"time":94752,"text":"political institutions like nation-states."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98251,"text":"And my suggestion is"},{"time":99955,"text":"that we change the subject,"},{"time":103576,"text":"that we stop talking about nations,"},{"time":107688,"text":"about bordered states,"},{"time":109104,"text":"and we start talking about cities."},{"time":113071,"text":"Because I think you will find, when we talk about cities,"},{"time":116429,"text":"we are talking about the political institutions"},{"time":120486,"text":"in which civilization and culture were born."},{"time":123307,"text":"We are talking about the cradle of democracy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":126472,"text":"We are talking about the venues in which"},{"time":129030,"text":"those public spaces where we come together"},{"time":132243,"text":"to create democracy, and at the same time"},{"time":136310,"text":"protest those who would take our freedom, take place."},{"time":141273,"text":"Think of some great names:"},{"time":143907,"text":"the Place de la Bastille,"},{"time":146600,"text":"Zuccotti Park,"},{"time":148567,"text":"Tahrir Square,"},{"time":150733,"text":"Taksim Square in today's headlines in Istanbul,"},{"time":155039,"text":"or, yes,"},{"time":157399,"text":"Tiananmen Square in Beijing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":160191,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":161897,"text":"Those are the public spaces"},{"time":164823,"text":"where we announce ourselves as citizens,"},{"time":168188,"text":"as participants, as people with the right"},{"time":171634,"text":"to write our own narratives."},{"time":175909,"text":"Cities are not only the oldest of institutions,"},{"time":178587,"text":"they're the most enduring."},{"time":180555,"text":"If you think about it,"},{"time":182727,"text":"Constantinople, Istanbul, much older than Turkey."},{"time":186696,"text":"Alexandria, much older than Egypt."},{"time":189806,"text":"Rome, far older than Italy."},{"time":193756,"text":"Cities endure the ages."},{"time":197364,"text":"They are the places where we are born,"},{"time":202147,"text":"grow up, are educated, work, marry,"},{"time":206483,"text":"pray, play, get old, and in time, die."},{"time":211342,"text":"They are home."},{"time":213470,"text":"Very different than nation-states,"},{"time":215526,"text":"which are abstractions."},{"time":216867,"text":"We pay taxes, we vote occasionally,"},{"time":220989,"text":"we watch the men and women we choose rule"},{"time":224364,"text":"rule more or less without us."},{"time":227588,"text":"Not so in those homes known as our towns"},{"time":231896,"text":"and cities where we live."},{"time":233695,"text":"Moreover, today, more than half of the world's population"},{"time":238744,"text":"live in cities."},{"time":240751,"text":"In the developed world, it's about 78 percent."},{"time":244723,"text":"More than three out of four people"},{"time":246718,"text":"live in urban institutions, urban places,"},{"time":250758,"text":"in cities today."},{"time":252366,"text":"So cities are where the action is."},{"time":255142,"text":"Cities are us. Aristotle said in the ancient world,"},{"time":258258,"text":"man is a political animal."},{"time":261839,"text":"I say we are an urban animal."},{"time":264866,"text":"We are an urban species, at home in our cities."},{"time":269731,"text":"So to come back to the dilemma,"},{"time":271883,"text":"if the dilemma is we have old-fashioned"},{"time":274401,"text":"political nation-states unable to govern the world,"},{"time":278185,"text":"respond to the global challenges that we face"},{"time":281199,"text":"like climate change,"},{"time":283359,"text":"then maybe it's time for mayors to rule the world,"},{"time":289401,"text":"for mayors and the citizens and the peoples they represent"},{"time":292610,"text":"to engage in global governance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":298495,"text":"When I say if mayors ruled the world,"},{"time":300326,"text":"when I first came up with that phrase,"},{"time":302594,"text":"it occurred to me that actually, they already do."},{"time":306500,"text":"There are scores of international, inter-city,"},{"time":311298,"text":"cross-border institutions, networks of cities"},{"time":315560,"text":"in which cities are already, quite quietly,"},{"time":318605,"text":"below the horizon, working together"},{"time":321432,"text":"to deal with climate change, to deal with security,"},{"time":324129,"text":"to deal with immigration,"},{"time":325517,"text":"to deal with all of those tough,"},{"time":327176,"text":"interdependent problems that we face."},{"time":329982,"text":"They have strange names:"},{"time":333438,"text":"UCLG,"},{"time":336808,"text":"United Cities and Local Governments;"},{"time":341434,"text":"ICLEI,"},{"time":343234,"text":"the International Council for Local Environmental Issues."},{"time":348750,"text":"And the list goes on:"},{"time":349960,"text":"Citynet in Asia; City Protocol, a new organization"},{"time":353507,"text":"out of Barcelona that is using the web"},{"time":356992,"text":"to share best practices among countries."},{"time":360069,"text":"And then all the things we know a little better,"},{"time":361485,"text":"the U.S. Conference of Mayors,"},{"time":362776,"text":"the Mexican Conference of Mayors,"},{"time":364812,"text":"the European Conference of Mayors."},{"time":368378,"text":"Mayors are where this is happening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373361,"text":"And so the question is,"},{"time":375890,"text":"how can we create a world"},{"time":377644,"text":"in which mayors and the citizens they represent"},{"time":381259,"text":"play a more prominent role?"},{"time":383725,"text":"Well, to understand that,"},{"time":386675,"text":"we need to understand why cities are special,"},{"time":390473,"text":"why mayors are so different"},{"time":392368,"text":"than prime ministers and presidents,"},{"time":393856,"text":"because my premise is that a mayor and a prime minister"},{"time":398204,"text":"are at the opposite ends of a political spectrum."},{"time":402483,"text":"To be a prime minister or a president,"},{"time":404891,"text":"you have to have an ideology,"},{"time":407050,"text":"you have to have a meta-narrative,"},{"time":409112,"text":"you have to have a theory of how things work,"},{"time":411634,"text":"you have to belong to a party."},{"time":413669,"text":"Independents, on the whole,"},{"time":415226,"text":"don't get elected to office."},{"time":416976,"text":"But mayors are just the opposite."},{"time":419209,"text":"Mayors are pragmatists, they're problem-solvers."},{"time":423658,"text":"Their job is to get things done, and if they don't,"},{"time":425621,"text":"they're out of a job."},{"time":428340,"text":"Mayor Nutter of Philadelphia said,"},{"time":431078,"text":"we could never get away here in Philadelphia"},{"time":434660,"text":"with the stuff that goes on in Washington,"},{"time":436970,"text":"the paralysis, the non-action, the inaction."},{"time":441985,"text":"Why? Because potholes have to get filled,"},{"time":446444,"text":"because the trains have to run,"},{"time":448343,"text":"because kids have to be able to get to school."},{"time":451292,"text":"And that's what we have to do,"},{"time":452588,"text":"and to do that is about pragmatism"},{"time":455527,"text":"in that deep, American sense,"},{"time":457499,"text":"reaching outcomes."},{"time":459429,"text":"Washington, Beijing, Paris, as world capitals,"},{"time":465538,"text":"are anything but pragmatic,"},{"time":468850,"text":"but real city mayors have to be pragmatists."},{"time":471769,"text":"They have to get things done,"},{"time":473493,"text":"they have to put ideology and religion and ethnicity aside"},{"time":476890,"text":"and draw their cities together."},{"time":479254,"text":"We saw this a couple of decades ago"},{"time":481924,"text":"when Teddy Kollek, the great mayor of Jerusalem"},{"time":484999,"text":"in the '80s and the '90s,"},{"time":487104,"text":"was besieged one day in his office"},{"time":490407,"text":"by religious leaders from all of the backgrounds,"},{"time":495070,"text":"Christian prelates, rabbis, imams."},{"time":497905,"text":"They were arguing with one another"},{"time":499404,"text":"about access to the holy sites."},{"time":501530,"text":"And the squabble went on and on,"},{"time":503309,"text":"and Kollek listened and listened,"},{"time":505151,"text":"and he finally said, \"Gentlemen,"},{"time":509453,"text":"spare me your sermons,"},{"time":511609,"text":"and I will fix your sewers.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":514653,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":515674,"text":"That's what mayors do."},{"time":517738,"text":"They fix sewers, they get the trains running."},{"time":521158,"text":"There isn't a left or a right way of doing."},{"time":523706,"text":"Boris Johnson in London calls himself an anarcho-Tory."},{"time":528183,"text":"Strange term, but in some ways, he is."},{"time":530058,"text":"He's a libertarian. He's an anarchist."},{"time":532491,"text":"He rides to work on a bike,"},{"time":533980,"text":"but at the same time, he's in some ways a conservative."},{"time":536827,"text":"Bloomberg in New York was a Democrat,"},{"time":540067,"text":"then he was a Republican,"},{"time":540885,"text":"and finally he was an Independent, and said"},{"time":542722,"text":"the party label just gets in the way."},{"time":545143,"text":"Luzhkov, 20 years mayor in Moscow,"},{"time":548258,"text":"though he helped found a party, United Party with Putin,"},{"time":551718,"text":"in fact refused to be defined by the party"},{"time":555014,"text":"and finally, in fact, lost his job not under Brezhnev,"},{"time":558304,"text":"not under Gorbachev, but under Putin,"},{"time":561177,"text":"who wanted a more faithful party follower."},{"time":565330,"text":"So mayors are pragmatists and problem-solvers."},{"time":569444,"text":"They get things done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":570817,"text":"But the second thing about mayors"},{"time":572226,"text":"is they are also what I like to call homeboys,"},{"time":576407,"text":"or to include the women mayors, homies."},{"time":579047,"text":"They're from the neighborhood."},{"time":581710,"text":"They're part of the neighborhood. They're known."},{"time":583517,"text":"Ed Koch used to wander around New York City"},{"time":585792,"text":"saying, \"How am I doing?\""},{"time":588308,"text":"Imagine David Cameron"},{"time":589963,"text":"wandering around the United Kingdom"},{"time":591913,"text":"asking, \"How am I doing?\" He wouldn't like the answer."},{"time":594391,"text":"Or Putin. Or any national leader."},{"time":597109,"text":"He could ask that because he knew New Yorkers"},{"time":599121,"text":"and they knew him."},{"time":600997,"text":"Mayors are usually from the places they govern."},{"time":604863,"text":"It's pretty hard to be a carpetbagger and be a mayor."},{"time":607667,"text":"You can run for the Senate out of a different state,"},{"time":609481,"text":"but it's hard to do that as a mayor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":612407,"text":"And as a result, mayors and city councillors"},{"time":615491,"text":"and local authorities"},{"time":617228,"text":"have a much higher trust level,"},{"time":619479,"text":"and this is the third feature about mayors,"},{"time":622007,"text":"than national governing officials."},{"time":624380,"text":"In the United States, we know the pathetic figures:"},{"time":627965,"text":"18 percent of Americans approve of Congress"},{"time":632424,"text":"and what they do."},{"time":633926,"text":"And even with a relatively popular president like Obama,"},{"time":637525,"text":"the figures for the Presidency run about 40, 45,"},{"time":640621,"text":"sometimes 50 percent at best."},{"time":642406,"text":"The Supreme Court has fallen way down from what it used to be."},{"time":645575,"text":"But when you ask, \"Do you trust your city councillor,"},{"time":649025,"text":"do you trust your mayor?\""},{"time":651201,"text":"the rates shoot up to 70, 75, even 80 percent,"},{"time":656354,"text":"because they're from the neighborhood,"},{"time":658499,"text":"because the people they work with are their neighbors,"},{"time":661416,"text":"because, like Mayor Booker in Newark,"},{"time":664833,"text":"a mayor is likely to get out of his car on the way to work"},{"time":668032,"text":"and go in and pull people out of a burning building --"},{"time":670786,"text":"that happened to Mayor Booker --"},{"time":673124,"text":"or intervene in a mugging in the street as he goes to work"},{"time":676065,"text":"because he sees it."},{"time":677397,"text":"No head of state would be permitted"},{"time":679780,"text":"by their security details to do it,"},{"time":681632,"text":"nor be in a position to do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":683850,"text":"That's the difference, and the difference"},{"time":685389,"text":"has to do with the character of cities themselves,"},{"time":687554,"text":"because cities are profoundly multicultural,"},{"time":694175,"text":"open, participatory, democratic,"},{"time":698510,"text":"able to work with one another."}]},{"cues":[{"time":701164,"text":"When states face each other,"},{"time":703990,"text":"China and the U.S., they face each other like this."},{"time":708280,"text":"When cities interact, they interact like this."},{"time":712883,"text":"China and the U.S., despite the recent"},{"time":716190,"text":"meta-meeting in California,"},{"time":718801,"text":"are locked in all kinds of anger, resentment, and rivalry"},{"time":723566,"text":"for number one."},{"time":724807,"text":"We heard more about who will be number one."},{"time":727784,"text":"Cities don't worry about number one."},{"time":729935,"text":"They have to work together, and they do work together."},{"time":732118,"text":"They work together in climate change, for example."},{"time":735729,"text":"Organizations like the C40, like ICLEI, which I mentioned,"},{"time":739235,"text":"have been working together"},{"time":741119,"text":"many, many years before Copenhagen."},{"time":743309,"text":"In Copenhagen, four or five years ago,"},{"time":745830,"text":"184 nations came together to explain to one another"},{"time":749224,"text":"why their sovereignty didn't permit them"},{"time":751469,"text":"to deal with the grave, grave crisis of climate change,"},{"time":755771,"text":"but the mayor of Copenhagen had invited"},{"time":759047,"text":"200 mayors to attend."},{"time":760769,"text":"They came, they stayed, and they found ways"},{"time":763829,"text":"and are still finding ways to work together,"},{"time":766920,"text":"city-to-city, and through inter-city organizations."},{"time":770369,"text":"Eighty percent of carbon emissions come from cities,"},{"time":774146,"text":"which means cities are in a position"},{"time":776030,"text":"to solve the carbon problem, or most of it,"},{"time":779238,"text":"whether or not the states of which they are a part"},{"time":782026,"text":"make agreements with one another."},{"time":784084,"text":"And they are doing it."},{"time":785332,"text":"Los Angeles cleaned up its port,"},{"time":787632,"text":"which was 40 percent of carbon emissions,"},{"time":790207,"text":"and as a result got rid of about 20 percent of carbon."},{"time":793988,"text":"New York has a program to upgrade its old buildings,"},{"time":796972,"text":"make them better insulated in the winter,"},{"time":800156,"text":"to not leak energy in the summer,"},{"time":802099,"text":"not leak air conditioning. That's having an impact."},{"time":805046,"text":"Bogota, where Mayor Mockus,"},{"time":806940,"text":"when he was mayor, he introduced a transportation system"},{"time":811176,"text":"that saved energy, that allowed surface buses"},{"time":815628,"text":"to run in effect like subways,"},{"time":817163,"text":"express buses with corridors."},{"time":819079,"text":"It helped unemployment, because people could get across town,"},{"time":822365,"text":"and it had a profound impact on climate as well as"},{"time":826221,"text":"many other things there."},{"time":827292,"text":"Singapore, as it developed its high-rises"},{"time":830146,"text":"and its remarkable public housing,"},{"time":831851,"text":"also developed an island of parks,"},{"time":835344,"text":"and if you go there, you'll see how much of it"},{"time":837060,"text":"is green land and park land."},{"time":838601,"text":"Cities are doing this, but not just one by one."},{"time":841109,"text":"They are doing it together."},{"time":842694,"text":"They are sharing what they do,"},{"time":846352,"text":"and they are making a difference by shared best practices."},{"time":850321,"text":"Bike shares, many of you have heard of it,"},{"time":851953,"text":"started 20 or 30 years ago in Latin America."},{"time":854256,"text":"Now it's in hundreds of cities around the world."},{"time":856600,"text":"Pedestrian zones, congestion fees,"},{"time":859891,"text":"emission limits in cities like California cities have,"},{"time":863601,"text":"there's lots and lots that cities can do"},{"time":865905,"text":"even when opaque, stubborn nations refuse to act."}]},{"cues":[{"time":875265,"text":"So what's the bottom line here?"},{"time":879233,"text":"The bottom line is, we still live politically"},{"time":882980,"text":"in a world of borders, a world of boundaries,"},{"time":885195,"text":"a world of walls,"},{"time":886793,"text":"a world where states refuse to act together."},{"time":892953,"text":"Yet we know that the reality we experience"},{"time":896746,"text":"day to day is a world without borders,"},{"time":900943,"text":"a world of diseases without borders"},{"time":903417,"text":"and doctors without borders,"},{"time":905717,"text":"maladies sans frontières, Médecins Sans Frontières,"},{"time":910289,"text":"of economics and technology without borders,"},{"time":916360,"text":"of education without borders,"},{"time":918476,"text":"of terrorism and war without borders."},{"time":921706,"text":"That is the real world, and unless we find a way"},{"time":924920,"text":"to globalize democracy or democratize globalization,"},{"time":930350,"text":"we will increasingly not only risk"},{"time":934718,"text":"the failure to address all of these transnational problems,"},{"time":938799,"text":"but we will risk losing democracy itself,"},{"time":942518,"text":"locked up in the old nation-state box,"},{"time":947144,"text":"unable to address global problems democratically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":952837,"text":"So where does that leave us?"},{"time":955831,"text":"I'll tell you. The road to global democracy"},{"time":958842,"text":"doesn't run through states."},{"time":960813,"text":"It runs through cities."},{"time":963375,"text":"Democracy was born in the ancient polis."},{"time":968175,"text":"I believe it can be reborn in the global cosmopolis."},{"time":973683,"text":"In that journey from polis to cosmopolis,"},{"time":977627,"text":"we can rediscover the power"},{"time":979898,"text":"of democracy on a global level."},{"time":982021,"text":"We can create not a League of Nations, which failed,"},{"time":986043,"text":"but a League of Cities,"},{"time":987431,"text":"not a United or a dis-United Nations,"},{"time":990543,"text":"but United Cities of the World."},{"time":992801,"text":"We can create a global parliament of mayors."},{"time":996888,"text":"That's an idea. It's in my conception of the coming world,"},{"time":1000984,"text":"but it's also on the table in City Halls"},{"time":1003666,"text":"in Seoul, Korea, in Amsterdam,"},{"time":1006394,"text":"in Hamburg, and in New York."},{"time":1008433,"text":"Mayors are considering that idea of how you can actually"},{"time":1011291,"text":"constitute a global parliament of mayors,"},{"time":1014450,"text":"and I love that idea, because a parliament of mayors"},{"time":1017330,"text":"is a parliament of citizens"},{"time":1019476,"text":"and a parliament of citizens is a parliament of us,"},{"time":1023371,"text":"of you and of me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1026502,"text":"If ever there were citizens without borders,"},{"time":1031292,"text":"I think it's the citizens of TED"},{"time":1033435,"text":"who show the promise to be those citizens without borders."},{"time":1036626,"text":"I am ready to reach out and embrace"},{"time":1041556,"text":"a new global democracy,"},{"time":1043882,"text":"to take back our democracy."},{"time":1046981,"text":"And the only question is,"},{"time":1049119,"text":"are you?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1051178,"text":"Thank you so much, my fellow citizens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1053161,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1064351,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}